      {
        "identifier": "main.product_analytics_stg.bi_output_product_analytics_jarek_tables_feature_retention_table",
        "description": [
          "This table holds our app feature usage as a snapshot fact table. It tracks in daily, weekly and monthly cohorts over time. The granularity of the table is GCID, Feature, CohortType, CohortID and Period. Period = 0 denotes starting point for a given user and cohort grain and if there is a corresponding row with Period = 1 then it means the user was retained in using this feature on eg. week 1 after initial use. \n",
          "\n",
          "\n",
          " It holds over 130 interactions that can be considered product features as well as most important interactions like login, copy or withdrawal. \n",
          "\n",
          "\n",
          "### Useful query patterns\n",
          "\n",
          "#### Get daily feature uses:\n",
          "\n",
          "SELECT \\*\n",
          "\n",
          "FROM main.product_analytics_stg.bi_output_product_analytics_jarek_tables_feature_retention_table\n",
          "\n",
          "WHERE (\\`Period\\` = 0.0) AND (\\`CohortType\\` = 'Daily')\n",
          "\n",
          "#### Get weekly retention rate for features for first week retention:\n",
          "\n",
          "SELECT\n",
          "\n",
          "  \\`Feature\\`,\n",
          "\n",
          "  COUNT(DISTINCT CASE WHEN (\\`Period\\` = 1.0) THEN (\\`gcid\\`) END) / COUNT(DISTINCT \\`gcid\\`) AS \\`retention_rate\\`\n",
          "\n",
          "FROM \\`main\\`.\\`product_analytics_stg\\`.\\`bi_output_product_analytics_jarek_tables_feature_retention_table\\`\n",
          "\n",
          "WHERE (\\`Period\\` BETWEEN 0.0 AND 1.0) AND (\\`CohortType\\` = 'Weekly')\n",
          "\n",
          "GROUP BY \\`Feature\\`"
        ],
        "column_configs": [
